dirchange - changes the current working directory

Description:
The 'dirchange' command changes the current working directory to the path provided as an argument. If no path is given, or if the directory cannot be accessed, an error message is shown.

Usage:
dirchange <directory_path>

Examples:
dirchange /home/user
dirchange ../Documents
dirchange # Error: No directory path provided.
dirchange /nonexistent # Error: could not change directory to '/nonexistent'.
